theorem
Th40: (for M being (Matrix of ( REAL )) holds (for p being (FinSequence of ( REAL )) holds (( len M ) = ( len p ) implies (for i holds (i in ( Seg ( len ( p * M ) ) ) implies ( ( p * M ) . i ) = ( p "*" ( Col (M,i) ) ))))))
proof
let M being (Matrix of ( REAL ));
let p being (FinSequence of ( REAL ));
assume that
A1: ( len M ) = ( len p );
A2: ( len ( p * M ) ) = ( len ( Line (( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ),1) ) ) by MATRIXR1:def 12
.= ( width ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) ) by MATRIX_1:def 7;
hereby
let i;
assume that
A3: i in ( Seg ( len ( p * M ) ) );
A4: ( width ( LineVec2Mx p ) ) = ( len M ) by A1,MATRIXR1:def 10;
then ( len ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) ) = ( len ( LineVec2Mx p ) ) by CKB49:1;
then ( len ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) ) = 1 by MATRIXR1:48;
then 1 in ( Seg ( len ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) ) ) by FINSEQ_1:1;
then [ 1,i ] in ( Indices ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) ) by A2,A3,CKB14:1;
then A5: ( ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) * (1,i) ) = ( ( Line (( LineVec2Mx p ),1) ) "*" ( Col (M,i) ) ) by A4,CKB49:1
.= ( p "*" ( Col (M,i) ) ) by MATRIXR1:48;
( ( Line (( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ),1) ) . i ) = ( ( ( LineVec2Mx p ) * M ) * (1,i) ) by A2,A3,MATRIX_1:def 7;
hence ( p "*" ( Col (M,i) ) ) = ( ( p * M ) . i ) by A5,MATRIXR1:def 12;
